[32m│[0m AHA! This is the key insight:                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The payload appears **AFTER the input tag closes** with a `>`:               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```html                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <input type=text name=name placeholder="Enter your name..." >                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m &lt;&#115;&#99;&#114;&#105;&#112;&#116;&gt;alert('XSS')&lt;/&#115;&#99;&#114 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ;&#105;&#112;&#116;&gt;>                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m When the browser renders this HTML:                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. It decodes the HTML entities: `&lt;` → `<`, `&#115;` → `s`, etc.          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. The decoded result becomes: `<script>alert('XSS')</script>`               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. This script tag is OUTSIDE the input tag, in the HTML body                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. The browser executes it!                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m So the XSS DOES execute client-side! The "Failed! Try again!" is just the    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m server's default message, but the JavaScript runs in the browser.            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Now I need to craft a payload that, when executed client-side, will reveal   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the flag. The flag might be:                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - In the DOM already (hidden)                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Retrieved by calling a specific function                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Shown when a specific condition is met                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
